addProposal(string).details: Adds a proposal named `desc` to the session

params._desc: description of the new proposal Emits a {ProposalRegistered} event. Requirements: - `_desc` cannot be empty - `msg.sender` should be a voter - `worklowStatus` should be WorkflowStatus.ProposalsRegistrationStarted

addVoter(address).details: Adds a new voter `_addr` to the session

params._addr: address to register Emits a {VoterRegistered} event. Requirements: - `address` cannot be already registered - `msg.sender` should be the owner - `worklowStatus` should be WorkflowStatus.RegisteringVoters

endProposalsRegistering().details: Sets the `workflowStatus` to `ProposalsRegistrationEnded` Emits a {WorkflowStatusChange} event. Requirements: - `workflowStatus` should be WorkflowStatus.ProposalsRegistrationStarted - `msg.sender` should be owner

endVotingSession().details: Sets the `workflowStatus` to `VotingSessionEnded` Emits a {WorkflowStatusChange} event. Requirements: - `workflowStatus` should be WorkflowStatus.VotingSessionStarted - `msg.sender` should be owner

getOneProposal(uint8).details: Gets the Proposal struct for a given `_id`

returns._0: Proposal Requirements: - `address` cannot be a non voter

getVoter(address).details: Gets the Voter struct of a given `_addr`

returns._0: Voter Requirements: - `address` cannot be a non voter

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._id: `proposalId` to vote for Emits a {Voted} event. Requirements: - `_id` should exists - `msg.sender` should be a voter - `worklowStatus` should be WorkflowStatus.VotingSessionStarted - `msg.sender` should be owner

startProposalsRegistering().details: Sets the `workflowStatus` to `ProposalsRegistrationStarted` Emits a {WorkflowStatusChange} event. Requirements: - `workflowStatus` should be WorkflowStatus.RegisteringVoters - `msg.sender` should be owner

startVotingSession().details: Sets the `workflowStatus` to `VotingSessionStarted` Emits a {WorkflowStatusChange} event. Requirements: - `workflowStatus` should be WorkflowStatus.ProposalsRegistrationEnded - `msg.sender` should be owner

tallyVotes().details: Tally the winner setting the `winningProposalId` Emits a {WorkflowStatusChange} event. Requirements: - `workflowStatus` should be WorkflowStatus.VotingSessionEnded - `msg.sender` should be owner
